  "prompt": "Who are the greatest pianists of our age?",
  "response": "Determining the greatest pianists of our age is subjective and can vary depending on personal preferences, musical tastes, and criteria for greatness. However, several pianists are frequently mentioned due to their exceptional skill, influence, and contributions to music. Here are a few who are often considered among the top:\n\n1. **Martha Argerich** - Renowned for her passionate and technically brilliant performances, she is widely regarded as one of the greatest pianists of the late 20th and early 21st centuries.\n\n2. **Lang Lang** - Known for his dynamic stage presence and virtuosic talent, Lang Lang has been a significant figure in bringing classical music to a broader audience.\n\n3. **Krystian Zimerman** - Acclaimed for his nuanced interpretations and technical precision, he is considered one of the leading pianists of his generation.\n\n4. **Evgeny Kissin** - A prodigy from a young age, Kissin is celebrated for his emotional depth and technical skill.\n\n5. **Yuja Wang** - Known for her extraordinary technique and vibrant performances, she has gained a reputation as one of the most exciting pianists of her generation.\n\n6. **Murray Perahia** - Distinguished for his elegant playing and comprehensive interpretations, Perahia is highly respected in the classical music community.\n\n7. **Grigory Sokolov** - Acclaimed for his profound musical insight and remarkable technical ability, Sokolov is revered by critics and audiences alike.\n\nThese pianists have significantly contributed to classical music and continue to inspire audiences worldwide. Of course, many other pianists are doing outstanding work, and opinions on who is \"the greatest\" can vary widely.",
